Step 1 – Baseline Neural Network

A baseline MLP using a 12-month look-back window was trained to predict β. The learning curve shows stable convergence without overfitting.

Discussion & Findings

Neural β estimates show weak and often negative correlation between cryptocurrencies and traditional markets. Equity factors show temporary influence, while Fama–French factors offer minor improvement in prediction accuracy. Overall, cryptocurrencies remain largely independent from traditional risk premia.
